During the course the students become familiar with current teaching materials, analyze existing exercise materials, methods, techniques and assessment models. The students create tasks and exercises using information technology tools and taking into account studying goals and age appropriateness. 6th grade standard determining test and basic school final exam in Estonian will be analyzed. Students assess and give feedback to different assignments submitted by pupils of general education schools.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Students can plan and give Estonian lessons to grades 5-9, consider the individuality of pupils, know the curriculum, teaching materials, principles of feedback and formative assessment.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  By the end of the course students
- can word the goals of teaching Estonian according to the national curriculum;
- know teaching materials and can create them;
- can plan and give lessons, considering the individuality of pupils, the possibilities of a modern learning environment, the principles of integration, special educational needs and the principles of formative assessment;
- can use different teaching methods considering teaching principles, the goals of study and the differences of learners
- can give supportive feedback to pupils.
